@NODE "main" "DiskInfoTools V2.0"
@TOC "MAIN"
=====================================================================
                D I S K   I N F O   T O O L S   V 2.0

                             B  Y

            S A N E   S O F T      S H A R E W A R E

                      Barney Blankenship
=====================================================================

   Tools to help you manage your disk space (and stay sane!).
        Without further introduction, the four tools are:

       @{" PieChart Directory Usage " LINK "piedir"} A nice utility if you use a
       colorful Workbench (be sure and show this one to your friends)

       @{" Duplicate Finder " LINK "dup"} Identifies the duplicate files on
       your disk(s).  Find out how redundant your files are.

       @{" Compare Directory " LINK "comp"} Something to compare two disks
       or directories. You may want to use this to verify what you
       put on a disk before mailing it.

       @{" Verify Directory " LINK "vdir"} Helps to detect a variety of problems
       ranging from file corruption to viruses.

- * - - * - - * - - * - - * - - * - - * - - * - - * - - * - - * - - * -

 If you had version 1.0, you may want to read: @{" What's New " LINK "new"}

